{
  "name": ".12.New",
  "lockfileVersion": 3,LP-04: Date Formatting Consistency
Field	Value
Description	TrainingView and other pages use toLocaleDateString('en-IN', {...}) for date formatting. The spec says "DD-MMM-YYYY format." Some pages format differently — no shared date formatting utility.
Root Cause	No centralized date format composable or utility.
Recommended Solution	Create a formatDate(date, format?) utility in src/utils/formatters.ts. Use it consistently across all Doer pages. Defined formats: 'short' (DD-MMM-YYYY), 'long' (DD Month YYYY), 'relative' ("2d ago"), 'time' (HH:MM).
Files to Update	src/utils/formatters.ts, all 11 Doer page files.
Dependencies	CR-04 (dynamic date)
Acceptance Criteria	All date displays across Doer use the same formatDate() utility. Format is consistent: "3 Jun 2026" not "03/06/2026".
Estimated Complexity	Small — 0.5 day
